department_name: Humboldt County Department of Health and Human Services Division of Environmental Health

grading_system.description: Grading system not definitively identified in official sources - violations are categorized as Critical Risk Factors (1-24), Major Violations, and Minor Violations, but specific scoring/grading methodology not found

inspection_details.frequency: Risk-based inspections occurring 1-3 times per year depending on facility type - DEH performs 1,400-1,500 routine inspections annually
inspection_details.reinspection_trigger: Non-routine inspections occur as needed, complaint-driven or at owner request
inspection_details.public_disclosure: Inspection reports available online within one week of inspection date with up to 1 year of history - available through online database and at physical locations

fire_safety_authority.ansul_system_requirements: Commercial kitchen hood fire suppression systems required per NFPA 17A standard - semi-annual inspections required

regulatory_framework.food_code_basis: California Retail Food Code (CalCode) - became effective July 1, 2007
regulatory_framework.state_vs_local_authority: County-level inspections conducted by Humboldt County Division of Environmental Health - excludes Ferndale city limits and tribal lands
regulatory_framework.local_ordinances: Follows state CalCode requirements - construction plans review required through Environmental Health
permit_types: Food Safety Manager Certification (required per CalCode 113947.1)

confidence_notes: Clear information available on inspection frequency, food code basis, and department structure. However, specific grading methodology (letter grades vs numerical scores vs pass/fail) could not be definitively determined from official sources.
verification_notes: Requires manual verification of: 1) Specific grading system methodology (A/B/C grades vs numerical scoring), 2) Exact point deduction system if numerical, 3) Grade posting requirements, 4) Re-inspection triggers for poor grades, 5) Specific fire department inspection requirements for commercial kitchens in Humboldt County
